<subSubSection id="8FA699C2FFFA866EFF49BEEDFB1DF947" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" type="description">
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFFA866EFF49BEEDFB1DF947" blockId="1.[136,1452,1094,2093]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
Evergreen, dioecious trees, 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFE0DBEECFDC4FB4E" box="[505,607,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="m" value="27.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="20.0">20–35 m</quantity>
tall, branching usually whorled, main trunk 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFB94BEECFB44FB4E" box="[1120,1247,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="cm" value="105.0" valueMax="120.0" valueMin="90.0">90–120 cm</quantity>
in diameter; bark rough, brown; exudate orange-red, viscous. Leaves alternate, petiolate; petiole 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFBF8BE88FB10FB72" box="[1036,1163,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="cm" value="3.85" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4.2 cm</quantity>
long, round to shallowly grooved, glabrous; lamina 8–10 × 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFDF7BEA4FDCCFA96" box="[515,599,1274,1301]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 cm</quantity>
, broadly lanceolate, apex acute to acuminate, margin undulate, base rounded, adaxially dark green, gland-dotted, abaxially glaucous, glabrous; midvein prominent, lateral veins not prominent, 8- 13 paired. Male inflorescence 2–3-flowered, axillary umbel; peduncle erect, 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFC15BF1CFB83FADE" box="[993,1048,1346,1373]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
long, cylindrical, scurfy tomentose. Flowers caducous, urceolate, longer than broad, 4.1-4.3 × 2.3–3.0 mm, brownish yellow, pedicellate; pedicel 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFAB6BF38FA37FA02" box="[1346,1452,1382,1409]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10 mm</quantity>
long, pubescent; bracteole 2.1–3.0 × 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFDDCBFD4FD2AFA26" box="[552,689,1418,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.2">2.2–3.1 mm</quantity>
, ovate, acute at apex, appressed to the base of male flower, dorsally convex, brownish yellow, densely pubescent outside, persistent. Perianth trilobed, equal, acute, curved outward, brownish yellow, densely pubescent outside; staminal column 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFCCCBF8CFC0FFA6E" box="[824,916,1490,1517]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
long, cylindrical, pilose up to anthers from base; anthers 12–13. Female inflorescence 2-flowered, axillary umbel; peduncle erect, 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFBECBFA8FBC1F992" box="[1048,1114,1526,1553]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, cylindrical, puberulous; flowers urceolate, 4.2–6.1 × 4.0–5.0 mm, yellow, persistent, pedicellate; pedicel up to 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFBBFBC44FB17F9B6" box="[1099,1164,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long, pubescent; perianth trilobed, equal, acute, curved outward, scabrid outside; stigma bilobed; ovary ovate, 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFB94BC60FB59F9DA" box="[1120,1218,1598,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, densely tomentose. Fruits usually solitary, rarely in pairs, dehiscent, 2.5–4.0 × 3.5–5.0 cm, subglobose to globose, brown, apex obtuse, base round, longitudinal suture on both sides, scurfy pubescent; rind 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFC63BCD8FB98F922" box="[919,1027,1670,1697]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10 mm</quantity>
thick, brown; seed 2.0–3.6 × 2.5–4.0 cm, oblong, black, arillate; aril partially covering seed, yellow turning orange-red, lacerate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FA699C2FFFA866EFF49BC90FC7BF96A" box="[189,992,1742,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFFA866EFF49BC90FC7BF96A" blockId="1.[136,1452,1094,2093]" box="[189,992,1742,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFF49BC90FEEEF96B" bold="true" box="[189,373,1742,1768]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">Distribution:—</emphasis>
Endemic to the southern Western Ghats at 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFCA6BC90FC47F96A" box="[850,988,1742,1769]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="m" value="1000.0" valueMax="1100.0" valueMin="900.0">900-1100 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FA699C2FFFA866EFF49BCACFC3CF88F" box="[189,935,1778,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFFA866EFF49BCACFC3CF88F" blockId="1.[136,1452,1094,2093]" box="[189,935,1778,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFF49BCACFEC4F88F" bold="true" box="[189,351,1778,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Flowering August–November, fruiting March–June.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FA699C2FFFA866EFF49BD48FCCFF8D7" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFFA866EFF49BD48FCCFF8D7" blockId="1.[136,1452,1094,2093]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFF49BD48FEFFF8B3" bold="true" box="[189,356,1814,1840]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">Etymology:—</emphasis>
Named in honour of Padma Shri Dr. P. Pushpangadan, former Director of JNTBGRI, Palode and CSIR-NBRI, Lucknow, 
<collectingCountry id="BFAB8AD9FFFA866EFE62BD64FE49F8D7" box="[406,466,1850,1876]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">India</collectingCountry>
, a renowned Indian ethnobotanist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FA699C2FFFA866DFF49BD00FEDFFD7A" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="263" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFFA866EFF49BD00FC9DF843" blockId="1.[136,1452,1094,2093]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFF49BD00FEBDF8FB" bold="true" box="[189,294,1886,1912]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">Notes:—</emphasis>
Based on detailed morphological evaluation and comparison with 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFBE0BD01FB36F8FB" box="[1044,1197,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFFA866EFBE0BD01FB32F8FB" authorityName="King" authorityYear="1891" box="[1044,1193,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beddomei">M. beddomei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
this subspecies differs in key characters, smaller leaves (7–10 × 
<quantity id="004467ACFFFA866EFDA2BDDCFD59F81E" box="[598,706,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="cm" value="4.25" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="3.0">3–5.5 cm</quantity>
), fewer lateral veins (8–13 pairs), more anthers (13), globose fruits and seeds partially covered by aril (
<figureCitation id="5F87D6CCFFFA866EFDE2BDF8FDC4F843" box="[534,607,1958,1984]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2018,2040]" captionTargetBox="[203,1411,217,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-25@4.[151,1436,190,1994]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myristica pushpangadaniana A. Twig with leaves and fruit. B. Dehisced fruit. C. Male flower. D. Androecium exposed. E. Female flower. F. Gynoecium exposed." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392646/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="5F87D6CCFFFA866EFD9FBDF8FDE1F843" box="[619,634,1958,1984]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,2032,2054]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,2007]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,190,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Myristica pushpangadaniana: A. Twig with leaves. B. Male inflorescence. C. Female inflorescence. D. Male flower. E. Androecium exposed. F. Female flower. G. Gynoecium exposed. H. Fruit. I. Arillate seed. J. Bark exudate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="5F87D6CCFFFA866EFD73BDF8FD03F843" box="[647,664,1958,1984]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[136,229,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox="[197,1400,203,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[178,1410,190,2004]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Subspecies of Myristica beddomei (Prior). A1–5. M. beddomei subsp. beddomei. B1–5. M. beddomei subsp. spherocarpa. C1–5: M. beddomei subsp. ustulata. 1. Twig with leaf. 2. Male flower. 3. Female flower. 4. Fruit. 5. Seed with aril" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392652" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">4</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="8A3EFFF2FFFA866EFD57BDF8FD6EF843" box="[675,757,1958,1984]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,880,904]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of M. beddomei and subspecies." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/93C39AC1FFF9866DFF7CB92EFD7BFC0B" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" tableUuid="93C39AC1FFF9866DFF7CB92EFD7BFC0B">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFFA866DFF49BD94FC9FFE37" blockId="1.[136,1452,1094,2093]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,832]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="263" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
The chemical profile of essential oils isolated from rind, aril, seed and leaf of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFFA866EFBD3BD95FAE7F867" authority="subsp. beddomei" box="[1063,1404,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="beddomei">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFBD3BD95FB21F867" box="[1063,1210,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFAFBBD94FAE7F867" box="[1295,1404,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">beddomei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFFA866EFF7CBDB1FE5FF78B" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[136,452,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="ustulata">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFF7CBDB1FE82F78B" box="[136,281,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFE9EBDB0FE5FF78B" box="[362,452,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found to be similar, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFFA866EFC77BDB1FB69F78B" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[899,1266,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFC77BDB1FB88F78B" box="[899,1043,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFB91BDB0FB69F78B" box="[1125,1266,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was different. In 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFFA866EFF7CB24DFE61F7AF" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[136,506,2066,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFF7CB24DFE82F7AF" box="[136,281,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFE9FB24CFE61F7AF" box="[363,506,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFFA866EFE0EB24CFE65F7AF" box="[506,510,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">,</emphasis>
monoterpenes, phenyl propanoids and aliphatic hydrocarbons were absent in the leaf and seed essential oil, whereas these compounds were present in 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFCBABAC1FB07FF3B" authority="subsp. beddomei" box="[846,1180,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="beddomei">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFCBABAC1FC44FF3B" box="[846,991,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFBDBBAC0FB07FF3B" box="[1071,1180,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">beddomei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFB3BBAC1FF79FF5F" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="ustulata">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB3BBAC1FAFBFF3B" box="[1231,1376,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFF7CBA9CFF79FF5F" box="[136,226,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the rind essential oil of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFDE6BA9DFCFFFF5F" authority="subsp. beddomei" box="[530,868,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="beddomei">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFDE6BA9DFD3FFF5F" box="[530,676,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFD03BA9CFCFFFF5F" box="[759,868,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">beddomei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFC6DBA9DFB40FF5F" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[921,1243,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="ustulata">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFC6DBA9DFBB0FF5F" box="[921,1067,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB8ABA9CFB40FF5F" box="[1150,1243,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB2FBA9CFB44FF5F" box="[1243,1247,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">,</emphasis>
E-caryophyellene and α-terpineol were the major compounds, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFCFABAB9FB11FE83" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[782,1162,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFCFABAB9FC38FE83" box="[782,931,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFC09BAB8FB11FE83" box="[1021,1162,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, E-nerolidol and linalool were the major compounds. Likewise, in the arils of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFD2FBB55FBB1FEA7" authority="subsp. beddomei" box="[731,1066,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="beddomei">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFD2FBB55FCFCFEA7" box="[731,871,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFC49BB54FBB1FEA7" box="[957,1066,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">beddomei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFB95BB55FA3CFEA7" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[1121,1447,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="ustulata">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB95BB55FB6FFEA7" box="[1121,1268,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFABEBB54FA3CFEA7" box="[1354,1447,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFA53BB54FA30FEA7" box="[1447,1451,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">,</emphasis>
α-humulene was the major compound followed by trans-α-bergamotene, to the contrary, E-caryophyellene and αhumulene were the major compounds in 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFDA8BB0DFC4DFEEF" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[604,982,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFDA8BB0DFD6AFEEF" box="[604,753,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFCBDBB0CFC4DFEEF" box="[841,982,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
giving it a distinct chemical profile. The dissimilarities of chemical profile in 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFDDEBB29FC39FE13" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[554,930,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFDDEBB29FD25FE13" box="[554,702,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFCE1BB28FC39FE13" box="[789,930,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
combined with the morphological differences are supporting evidence for its elevation to species level.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFF9866DFF49BBE0FEDFFD7A" blockId="2.[136,1452,158,832]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
Petiole cross sections of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFE17BBE1FCD8FE5B" authority="subsp. beddomei" box="[483,835,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="beddomei">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFE17BBE1FDE2FE5B" box="[483,633,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFD22BBE0FCD8FE5B" box="[726,835,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">beddomei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFC76BBE1FB54FE5B" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[898,1231,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="ustulata">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFC76BBE1FB83FE5B" box="[898,1048,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB81BBE0FB54FE5B" box="[1141,1231,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were grooved and glabrous. That of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFEB8BBBDFD26FE7F" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[332,701,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFEB8BBBDFE46FE7F" box="[332,477,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFDC4BBBCFD26FE7F" box="[560,701,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was round to shallowly grooved and had epidermal trichomes. Five vascular bundles were observed in 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFDE8B859FCECFDA3" authority="subsp. beddomei" box="[540,887,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="beddomei">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFDE8B859FD2AFDA3" box="[540,689,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFCFEB858FCECFDA3" box="[778,887,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">beddomei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFC46B859FB67FDA3" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[946,1276,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="ustulata">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFC46B859FBDDFDA3" box="[946,1094,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB6BB858FB67FDA3" box="[1183,1276,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB08B858FA9BFDA3" box="[1276,1280,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">,</emphasis>
two at adaxial side, one at abaxial side and one each on each side. A lunar 
<typeStatus id="180774EBFFF9866DFCDDB875FCC2FDC6" box="[809,857,555,581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">type</typeStatus>
of arrangement of phloem patches occurs in the pith region. The anatomical features of the petiole of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFD53B811FB81FDEB" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[679,1050,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFD53B811FCA2FDEB" box="[679,825,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFC79B810FB81FDEB" box="[909,1050,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found different from the other two subspecies. The petiole was almost circular in outline with shallow groove. Three vascular bundles are enclosed in separate sclerenchyma patches, one large in the pith region and a small vascular bundle on each side. The anatomical characters in the petiole of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFE47B8E5FC93FD57" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" box="[435,776,698,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="spherocarpa">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFE47B8E5FDDFFD57" box="[435,580,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFD8FB8E4FC93FD57" box="[635,776,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">spherocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct from that of 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFBE3B8E5FAD7FD57" authority="ssp. beddomei" box="[1047,1356,698,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="beddomei">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFBE3B8E5FB32FD57" box="[1047,1193,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. beddomei</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFB2BB8E4FAD7FD57" box="[1247,1356,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">beddomei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00BCB1CAFFF9866DFA75B8E5FF79FD7B" authorityName="de Wilde" authorityYear="1997" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Myristica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="beddomei" subSpecies="ustulata">
ssp. 
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFF7CB880FF79FD7B" box="[136,226,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="5F87D6CCFFF9866DFF06B880FEADFD7A" box="[242,310,734,761]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[136,229,627,649]" captionTargetBox="[184,1389,214,574]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1436,190,602]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Diagrammatic representation of vasculature in petiole (CS) of M. beddomei and its subspecies." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392654" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392654/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FA699C2FFF9866DFF49B95CFA99FCC3" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="C703CA49FFF9866DFF49B95CFA99FCC3" blockId="2.[136,1452,158,832]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFF49B95CFDBFFC9F" bold="true" box="[189,548,770,796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Other specimens examined:—</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="77D4C014FFF9866DFDD7B95CFB65FCC3" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3744197302" collectingDate="2019-04" collectingDateMax="2019-05" collectingDateMin="2019-04" country="India" location="Thirunelveli district" municipality="Near Agasthyarkoodam" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kerala">
<emphasis id="F5C8165BFFF9866DFDD7B95CFDECFC9F" bold="true" box="[547,631,770,796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
<collectingCountry id="BFAB8AD9FFF9866DFDD7B95CFDECFC9F" box="[547,631,770,796]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">INDIA</collectingCountry>
